This transforms the inequality into \( |u - 1| + |v - 1| \le 1 \) where \( u \ge 0 \) and \( v \ge 0 \). 1. **Analyzing the transformed inequality**: - The inequality \( |u - 1| + |v - 1| \le 1 \) forms a diamond (a square rotated 45 degrees) centered at \( (1, 1) \) with vertices at \( (0, 1) \), \( (1, 0) \), \( (2, 1) \), and \( (1, 2) \). - The area of this diamond in the \( uv \)-plane is calculated by considering the vertices and the geometry of the diamond. The area is found to be 2. 2. **Mapping back to the \( xy \)-plane**: - Each point \( (u, v) \) in the \( uv \)-plane corresponds to four points \( (\pm u, \pm v) \) in the \( xy \)-plane due to the absolute values \( |x| \) and \( |y| \). - The region in the \( xy \)-plane is symmetric across both the \( x \)-axis and \( y \)-axis. Therefore, the total area in the \( xy \)-plane is four times the area in the first quadrant of the \( uv \)-plane. 3. **Calculating the total area**: - The area in the first quadrant of the \( uv \)-plane is 2, so multiplying by 4 (for all four quadrants) gives the total area as \( 4 \times 2 = 8 \). Thus, the area of the region defined by the inequality \( ||x| - 1| + ||y| - 1| \le 1 \) is \(\boxed{8}\).
